bug.summary: Style Transfer: model.__repr__() on model loaded from 5.8 throws error
bug.description:
Repro steps:
Load a model trained in Turi Create 5.8 into 6.0rc1.
Run print(model) in Python.
Actual output: <denchmark-code>KeyError: 'Field "_training_time_as_string" not in model. Available fields are batch_size, max_iterations, model, num_styles.' </denchmark-code>
Expected output: No error.
